translate spanish d10c_sair_47c9e0c6:

    # C "Anyway, he's been missing for a few days. I know that he is here somewhere. This isn't the first time he's visiting this place."
    C "De todos modos, lleva unos días desaparecido. Sé que está aquí en alguna parte. No es la primera vez que visita este lugar."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4552
translate spanish d10c_sair_63ac192e:

    # C "My name's Sair by the way. Nice to meet you."
    C "Por cierto, me llamo Sair. Encantado de conocerte."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4556
translate spanish d10c_sair_549d75fd:

    # S "What do I look like then, if not threatening?"
    S "¿Qué aspecto tengo entonces, si no es amenazante?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4559
translate spanish d10c_sair_2011f127:

    # C "{i}*chuckles*{/i} Well, nice and pretty are two things I thought immediately."
    C "{i}*risilla*{/i} Bueno, agradable y bonito son dos cosas que pensé inmediatamente."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4560
translate spanish d10c_sair_cf17cf4a:

    # C "Name's Sair by the way. It's nice to meet you."
    C "Por cierto, me llamo Sair. Encantado de conocerte."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4564
translate spanish d10c_sair_68df3116:

    # S "You seem way too relaxed for a place like this."
    S "Pareces demasiado relajado para un lugar como éste."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4565
translate spanish d10c_sair_315eb406:

    # S "Have you not seen all the mummies around here? Where {i}are{/i} your weapons?"
    S "¿No has visto todas las momias que hay por aquí? ¿Dónde {i}están{/i} tus armas?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4566
translate spanish d10c_sair_0ee66038:

    # Sw "Who knows what else is around."
    Sw "Quién sabe qué más hay por aquí."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4569
translate spanish d10c_sair_8b9ea3ae:

    # C "Yeah, you're right. But I think we're fine, when I came here, there was no one around at all."
    C "Sí, tienes razón. Pero creo que estamos bien, cuando vine aquí, no había nadie en ningún sitio."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4570
translate spanish d10c_sair_894686b5:

    # C "Name's Sair by the way."
    C "Por cierto, me llamo Sair."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4578
translate spanish d10c_sair2_313b9315:

    # S "[S]."
    S "[S]."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4582
translate spanish d10c_sair2_2a74c062:

    # Sa "Hi [S]."
    Sa "Hola [S]."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4586
translate spanish d10c_sair2_971a98df:

    # S "..."
    S "..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4592
translate spanish d10c_sair3_d2b8ba83:

    # Sa "So, anyway, look... my father has to be around here somewhere."
    Sa "En fin, mira...  Mi padre tiene que estar por aquí."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4593
translate spanish d10c_sair3_d3e71d05:

    # Sa "I don't know if he needs help or if he has other reasons not to come home."
    Sa "No sé si necesita ayuda o si tiene otras razones para no volver a casa."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4596
translate spanish d10c_sair3_d91729e0:

    # Sa "He has been to other places like this before. I mean, he's experienced."
    Sa "Ya ha estado en otros lugares como éste. Tiene experiencia."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4599
translate spanish d10c_sair3_ba1645e2:

    # S "Maybe something happened to him."
    S "Quizá le haya pasado algo."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4600
translate spanish d10c_sair3_15370171:

    # S "Are you sure it's a good idea for you to look for him?"
    S "¿Estás seguro de que es una buena idea que lo busques?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4603
translate spanish d10c_sair3_ad441eb3:

    # Sa "My mother said the same; she also warned me not to go."
    Sa "Mi madre dijo lo mismo; también me advirtió que no fuera."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4604
translate spanish d10c_sair3_6f9e1404:

    # Sa "But I am done waiting for the right moment to go."
    Sa "Pero ya he terminado de esperar el momento adecuado para ir."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4605
translate spanish d10c_sair3_f6fba881:

    # Sa "If my father needs help, I am going to be there for him. I will make him proud."
    Sa "Si mi padre necesita ayuda, voy a estar ahí para él. Haré que se sienta orgulloso."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4608
translate spanish d10c_sair3_2726d09a:

    # Sa "Anyway, I told you he has been here before. Before it became a Zone even. He had a safe space here."
    Sa "De todos modos, ya te he dicho que él ya ha estado aquí antes. Incluso antes de que se convirtiera en una Zona. El aquí tenía un lugar seguro."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4609
translate spanish d10c_sair3_90ad2f1e:

    # Sa "He told me roughly where it was, so that's how I knew to come here in the first place."
    Sa "Me dijo más o menos dónde estaba, así que por eso supe que debía venir aquí en primer lugar."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4612
translate spanish d10c_sair3_297a92e8:

    # S "If you knew where to come look for him, why haven't you found him yet?"
    S "Si sabías dónde venir a buscarlo, ¿por qué no lo has encontrado todavía?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4615
translate spanish d10c_sair3_54b72b4c:

    # Sa "I told you, I just got here. Tell you what... if you help me find him, I am sure I can convince him to reward you."
    Sa "Te lo dije, acabo de llegar. Te diré una cosa... si me ayudas a encontrarlo, seguro que puedo convencerle de que te recompense."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4616
translate spanish d10c_sair3_39afc47b:

    # Sa "He's been looting this place for a while now."
    Sa "Lleva un tiempo saqueando este lugar."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4620
translate spanish d10c_sair3_14ecebb8:

    # Sa "So, what do you say, [S]?"
    Sa "Entonces, ¿qué dices, [S]?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4622
translate spanish d10c_sair3_43ff3875:

    # Sa "So, what do you say?"
    Sa "Entonces, ¿qué dices?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4627
translate spanish d10c_sair3_eb53b140:

    # S "Okay, we can try, I guess."
    S "Vale, podemos intentarlo, supongo."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4628
translate spanish d10c_sair3_af710138:

    # Sa "Great, I am glad we met. You look badass, by the way-. {w=1.0}{nw}{a=jump:d10c_sair3_aftermath}"
    Sa "Genial, me alegro de que nos hayamos conocido. Por cierto, tienes un aspecto increíble-. {w=1.0}{nw}{a=jump:d10c_sair3_aftermath}"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4632
translate spanish d10c_sair3_839f53bb:

    # S "Sorry, you're on your own. I have other things to do"
    S "Lo siento, estás por tu cuenta. Tengo otras cosas que hacer"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4635
translate spanish d10c_sair3_bdc5111d:

    # Sa "I... I see."
    Sa "Yo...  Ya veo."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4636
translate spanish d10c_sair3_9d5a1ecd:

    # Sa "Well then, it was nice meeting you-.{w=1.0}{nw}{a=jump:d10c_sair3_aftermath}"
    Sa "Bueno, pues ha sido un placer conocerte-.{w=1.0}{nw}{a=jump:d10c_sair3_aftermath}"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4649
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_a3c68a48:

    # S "...!"
    S "¡...!"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4650
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_3b8897bf:

    # Sa "...aah...?!"
    Sa "¡¿¡... aaah...?!"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4652
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_2459b1f7:

    # "Suddenly, an arrow pierces Sair's head..."
    "De repente, una flecha atraviesa la cabeza de Sair..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4653
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_25de5ef8:

    # "In the distance, you hear a voice echo..."
    "En la distancia, se oye el eco de una voz..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4654
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_0a17d4f0:

    # C2 "Bullseye!"
    C2 "¡Diana!"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4659
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_9f74e839:

    # Sa "[S]... I... don't feel so good..."
    Sa "[S]...  Yo... no me siento muy bien..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4661
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_3b72ce3a:

    # Sa "I... don't... feel so good..."
    Sa "Yo... no... me siento muy bien..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4662
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_f9140d08:

    # St "What the fuck?!"
    St "¿Qué coño?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4666
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_1ff0fe3a:

    # Sa "I feel... tired..."
    Sa "Me siento... cansado..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4667
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_c8b49eef:

    # Sa "Need to... re..."
    Sa "Necesito... des..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4671
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_b45351bf:

    # St "Fucking shit!"
    St "¡Jodida Mierda!"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4672
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_968b0434:

    # Sw "Sair... I'm..."
    Sw "Sair...  Yo..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4673
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_7a08c5cd:

    # Sa "This is... I will find you, dad..."
    Sa "Esto es... yo te encontraré, papá..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4674
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_3e23bcac:

    # Sa "Just... a... minute..."
    Sa "Sólo... un... minuto..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4675
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_2493b360:

    # C2 "How is the fucker still moving?!"
    C2 "¿Cómo se mueve todavía el cabrón?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4678
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_60f3b778:

    # C3 "Is he talking to someone?"
    C3 "¿Está hablando con alguien?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4679
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_0c655462:

    # C2 "I can't see shit from here, let's get closer."
    C2 "No puedo ver nada desde aquí, acerquémonos."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4682
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_926f15d0:

    # St "I need to leave now."
    St "Necesito salir ahora."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4686
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_d56912fd:

    # "As they come skulking over, all they find is Sair's body."
    "Al acercarse sigilosamente, sólo encuentran el cuerpo de Sair."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4687
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_54a269a4:

    # "Trying not to make too much noise, you quickly rush towards another exit of the building..."
    "Tratando de no hacer demasiado ruido, se precipita rápidamente hacia la otra salida del edificio..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4690
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_68462a20:

    # St "Damn it, where do I even go?"
    St "Joder, ¿adónde voy?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4691
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_768e4e1b:

    # St "I should try to find that shelter he was talking about."
    St "Debería intentar encontrar ese refugio del que él hablaba."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4694
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_61138058:

    # St "{i}*sigh* Please don't be in there..."
    St "{i}*suspiro* Por favor, no estés ahí..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4697
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_79c3ed1d:

    # St "Hotel... that's what they called taverns, right?"
    St "Hotel...  Así se llamaban las posadas, ¿no?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4698
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_7a601e2a:

    # St "Maybe..."
    St "Tal vez..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4701
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_6b303234:

    # St "It's quite small. I could start looking there."
    St "Es bastante pequeño. Podría empezar a buscar allí."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4704
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_db8706d6:

    # "Moving towards the ruined building, the assailants can be heard crowding Sair's body, intent on plundering it..."
    "Avanzando hacia el edificio en ruinas, se oye a los asaltantes agolparse en el cuerpo de Sair, con la intención de saquearlo..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4710
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_ab0001b4:

    # St "This place is in a terrible state..."
    St "Este lugar está en un estado terrible..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4714
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_a46f3c44:

    # St "...but what choice do I have..."
    St "... pero qué opción tengo..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4718
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_f7e743a5:

    # "Entering the building, the creeping darkness takes a while to adjust to."
    "Al entrar en el edificio, cuesta un poco acostumbrarse a la oscuridad que se extiende."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4721
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_9416a1f5:

    # St "A real tavern with rooms and everything? Must have been nice, back in the day."
    St "¿Una verdadera posada con habitaciones y todo? Debió de ser agradable, en su día."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4722
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_36ac7bcf:

    # "A broken staircase leads upstairs, to quarters that from the current vantage point, seem to be in an equally bad state."
    "Una escalera rota conducía al piso superior, a unas dependencias que, desde el punto de vista actual, parecían estar en un estado igualmente malo."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4723
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_9b75feaf:

    # St "If he had some kind of shelter here, it must have been well hidden..."
    St "Si tenía algún tipo de refugio aquí, debe de estar bien escondido..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4724
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_4590501e:

    # St "\"Staffroom\"...whatever that means."
    St "\"Sala del Personal\"... lo que sea que eso signifique."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4725
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_ed41fba7:

    # "The entry to the room is sealed by an incongruously sturdy looking door that takes a while to unlock. Upon entering it, something becomes immediately clear..."
    "La entrada a la habitación está sellada por una puerta de aspecto incongruentemente robusto que tarda en abrirse. Al entrar en ella, algo queda inmediatamente claro..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4728
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_4c0ad56f:

    # St "Jackpot!"
    St "¡El premio gordo!"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4732
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_2a7fc6b2:

    # St "This must be the place..."
    St "Este debe ser el lugar..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4733
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_d9ee2f47:

    # St "What the hell! What is fueling these lights?"
    St "¿Qué demonios? ¿Qué es lo que alimenta estas luces?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4734
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_d587179d:

    # St "And what is..."
    St "Y qué es..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4737
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_c449766c:

    # "There's a strong smell that's easily recognisable."
    "Hay un fuerte olor que es fácilmente reconocible."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4738
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_7293dbe8:

    # St "Urgh... this.. really is the place."
    St "Urgh... este... es realmente el lugar."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4741
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_0dedf788:

    # St "How long has he been here?"
    St "¿Cuánto tiempo llevará aquí?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4742
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_04eb821b:

    # St "Ugh, the stench!"
    St "¡Uf, el hedor!"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4743
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_739ab7f7:

    # St "Yeah, this is definitely him. I can see the resemblance with Sair."
    St "Sí, definitivamente es él. Puedo ver el parecido con Sair."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4744
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_3431a35c:

    # St "Poor guys."
    St "Pobrecillos."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4747
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_8e96276c:

    # "Stepping closer..."
    "Acercándose más..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4750
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_e2331887:

    # Sw "Just what happened to you, old man..."
    Sw "Lo que te ha pasado, viejo..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4752
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_e246992d:

    # S "...?"
    S "¿...?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4755
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_971a98df:

    # S "..."
    S "..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4761
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_1a6f7e91:

    # St "Did Sair's father leave this note?"
    St "¿El padre de Sair dejó esta nota?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4764
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_8aa28f70:

    # St "Whatever story he has to tell can wait, first I have to get him out of here. The stench is unbearable."
    St "Sea cual sea la historia que tenga que contar, primero tengo que sacarlo de aquí. El hedor es insoportable."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4767
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_4ee8b62f:

    # "The body has a pungent, acrid smell, and grappling it to drag it away is not a simple task, as the dead weight slumps repeatedly against the rough floorboards."
    "El cuerpo tiene un olor fuerte y desagradable, y agarrarlo para arrastrarlo no es una tarea sencilla, ya que el peso de la muerte se desploma repetidamente contra las ásperas tablas del suelo."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4768
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_0f2ffa0a:

    # St "You're... heavy..."
    St "Eres... pesado..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4769
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_35fc4bb6:

    # St "Now where do I drop you..."
    St "Ahora dónde te dejo..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4770
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_820c6475:

    # "As the heavy door opens, it is clear that the corpse can't be simply dumped in front of the building."
    "Al abrirse la pesada puerta, queda claro que el cadáver no puede ser simplemente arrojado frente al edificio."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4771
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_0037e635:

    # St "I can't risk these guys finding him anywhere close to the safe room. Maybe one of the rooms upstairs."
    St "No puedo arriesgarme a que estos tipos lo encuentren cerca de la habitación segura. Quizá en una de las habitaciones de arriba."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4775
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_6cd5be22:

    # "Back in the hallway, the stairs creak under the weight, but they don't break. The upstairs hallway, littered with rubbish and fallen debris, leads to multiple rooms."
    "De vuelta al pasillo, las escaleras crujen bajo el peso, pero no se rompen. El pasillo de arriba, plagado de basura y escombros caídos, conduce a varias habitaciones."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4776
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_c6f9e626:

    # St "The first one will do..."
    St "La primera servirá..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4780
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_38a9fc5b:

    # "After opening the door, a cloud of dust spreads in the air..."
    "Tras abrir la puerta, una nube de polvo se extiende en el aire..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4781
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_18e61f14:

    # St "There... you... go..."
    St "Aquí... te... quedas..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4783
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_76b57807:

    # St "Rest in peace, I guess..."
    St "Descansa en paz, supongo..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4789
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_971a98df_1:

    # S "..."
    S "..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4795
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_971a98df_2:

    # S "..."
    S "..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4799
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_3f252b13:

    # St "Time to make myself a little more at home and unpack my gear..."
    St "Hora de sentirme un poco más como en casa y deshacer mi equipo..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4801
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_39e0278a:

    # "A short while later..."
    "Poco después..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4802
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_d7d25c33:

    # St "Rule number seven, always make sure your equipment is in working order and ready at a moment's notice."
    St "Regla número siete, asegúrate siempre de que tu equipo está en funcionamiento y listo en un momento dado."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4805
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_43ca57be:

    # S "Hm..."
    S "Hm..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4808
translate spanish d10c_sair3_aftermath_1d861952:

    # S "That should do it."
    S "Con eso debería bastar."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4812
translate spanish abrax_map_43ca57be:

    # S "Hm..."
    S "Hm..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4813
translate spanish abrax_map_60441e5a:

    # St "The map shows the industrial area that was previously buried under the sands."
    St "El mapa muestra la zona industrial que antes estaba enterrada bajo las arenas."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4814
translate spanish abrax_map_95f09f23:

    # St "If Sair's father was right, I will be able to find the newly revealed area if..."
    St "Si el padre de Sair tenía razón, podré encontrar la zona recién revelada si..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4821
translate spanish abrax_map_c23e2a4b:

    # St "...I follow the vegetation."
    St "... sigo la vegetación."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4825
translate spanish abrax_map_d0897aac:

    # "Much like indicated in the notes, patches of fog eventually rise over the road..."
    "Tal y como se indica en las notas, se levantan manchas de niebla sobre el camino..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4829
translate spanish abrax_map_687cc9c9:

    # St "This place is... strangely beautiful."
    St "Este lugar es... extrañamente hermoso."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4830
translate spanish abrax_map_70838da8:

    # St "I've never seen these kinds of trees."
    St "Nunca he visto este tipo de árboles."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4831
translate spanish abrax_map_d000bf7a:

    # "The trees lining the paved road shift gently in the breeze. The leaves are in all shapes and colours, as if every tree followed a different season."
    "Los árboles que bordean el camino pavimentado se mueven suavemente con la brisa. Las hojas tienen todas las formas y colores, como si cada árbol siguiera una estación diferente."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4832
translate spanish abrax_map_7296ec98:

    # "To each side of the road, humid, brown soil offers a stark contrast to the fine barren sands of the dunes around the Zone."
    "A cada lado de la carretera, la tierra húmeda y marrón ofrece un marcado contraste con las finas arenas estériles de las dunas que rodean la Zona."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4835
translate spanish abrax_map_015e2aee:

    # "Walking under a canopy of spontaneous vegetation is a new experience, alien to anybody born in a region where every plant is carefully tended and grown for the fruits it bears."
    "Caminar bajo un dosel de vegetación espontánea es una experiencia nueva, ajena a cualquiera que haya nacido en una región donde cada planta se cuida y cultiva cuidadosamente por los frutos que da."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4836
translate spanish abrax_map_66ca19a1:

    # "Neither Old Cairo, Zeta or any of the other ruins in the area could offer such an experience."
    "Ni el Viejo Cairo, ni Zeta o cualquiera de las otras ruinas de la zona podrían ofrecer una experiencia semejante."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4837
translate spanish abrax_map_a65160f5:

    # "Observing the ruins, it becomes difficult to date them, to distinguish the original ruins from whatever construct the Zone brought with it, real, tangible or based on sensory deception."
    "Observando las ruinas, resulta difícil datarlas, distinguir las ruinas originales de cualquier construcción que la Zona haya traído consigo, real, tangible o basada en el engaño sensorial."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4838
translate spanish abrax_map_21ba0a71:

    # "On the barks of the trees, insects roam and strive to reach the leaves high along the branches, fungi grow at the bases of some of the trees, bugs and other flying insects flutter from one tree to the next."
    "En las cortezas de los árboles, los insectos deambulan y se esfuerzan por alcanzar las hojas en lo alto de las ramas, los hongos crecen en las bases de algunos de los árboles, los bichos y otros insectos voladores revolotean de un árbol a otro."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4839
translate spanish abrax_map_743ea7f4:

    # "At a first observation, the fog would be in tune with the surrounding vegetation, but it still contributes to an atmosphere of eerie unease."
    "En una primera observación, la niebla estaría en sintonía con la vegetación circundante, pero sigue contribuyendo a una atmósfera de inquietud espeluznante."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4840
translate spanish abrax_map_4d2a8729:

    # "In a way, a natural phenomenon that is so profoundly out of place, much like the ecosystem that is surrounding this paved walkway, makes the experience more unsettling."
    "En cierto modo, un fenómeno natural tan profundamente fuera de lugar, como el ecosistema que rodea a este paseo pavimentado, hace que la experiencia sea más inquietante."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4841
translate spanish abrax_map_ef98f6ab:

    # "In the distance, beyond the field of vision, the lament of hound-like creatures is impossible to pinpoint."
    "En la distancia, más allá del campo de visión, el lamento de unas criaturas parecidas a los sabuesos es imposible de precisar."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4842
translate spanish abrax_map_f763d7b6:

    # St "I am not safe here. I have a feeling that it's not as peaceful here as it looks."
    St "No estoy a salvo aquí. Tengo la sensación de que esto no es tan pacífico como parece."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4845
translate spanish abrax_map_1724cf38:

    # "Eventually, as the walkway proceeds further in the distance, a dilapidated building appears in sight, alongside it."
    "Finalmente, a medida que la pasarela avanza en la distancia, aparece a la vista, junto a ella, un edificio en ruinas."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4846
translate spanish abrax_map_93990961:

    # St "Didn't I just leave the residential area?"
    St "¿Acaso no acabo de salir de la zona residencial?"

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4849
translate spanish abrax_map_a2835d51:

    # "Heavily weathered by time, and with a few other ruins close by, the nearest construction looks like the remains of a checkpoint, maybe an old demarcation to separate different areas of the ancient settlement..."
    "Muy erosionada por el tiempo, y con algunas otras ruinas cerca, la construcción más cercana parece los restos de un puesto de control, tal vez una antigua demarcación para separar diferentes zonas del antiguo asentamiento..."

# game/scripts/day10.rpy:4850
translate spanish abrax_map_a4c5db4e:

